# Business Context

Most organizations collect customer information through multiple systems instead of storing everything in one place.

For example, the sales team knows what a customer purchased, the support team knows what issues they reported, and the marketing team knows which campaigns they interacted with. Looking at these datasets individually provides only a partial view of the customer.

The goal of this project is to combine those datasets into a single analytical view.

With this unified view, business users can answer questions such as:

- Which customers generate the highest revenue?
- Which products are performing well?
- Which customers have raised multiple support tickets?
- How are customers responding to marketing campaigns?

Instead of searching through multiple systems, analysts can retrieve this information with SQL queries using Amazon Athena.

Although this project uses sample datasets, the same architecture can be applied to larger business environments where customer data needs to be analyzed efficiently.
